<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="chromatin">Chromatin</a> - Is a method of organising and highly compacting <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a>. It is formed from a <a href="#complex">complex</a> of various <a href="#molecule">molecules</a> including <a href="#protein">proteins</a>, <a href="#rna">RNA</a>, and of course <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a>. Chromatin can be organised into two different forms; one which composes the other. <a href="#euchromatin">Euchromatin</a> and <a href="#heteroChromatin">heterochromatin</a> respectively.